Problem: Container With Most Water
Topic: Arrays, Two Pointers
Difficulty: Medium

Approach:
Use two pointers starting from both ends. Calculate area using minimum height and width. Move the pointer with smaller height to maximize area.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int maxArea(vector<int>& height) {
        int left=0;
        int right=height.size()-1;
        int max_area=0;

        while(left<right){
        int curr_ht=min(height[left],height[right]);
        int curr_width=right-left;
        int curr_area=curr_ht*curr_width;

        max_area=max(max_area,curr_area);
        
        if(height[left]<height[right]){
            left++;
        }
        else{
            right--;
        }
        }
        return max_area;
    }
};
